# Accepted vulnerabilities — reviewed, no compatible fix, tracked for remediation.
#
# starlette HIGH advisories (transitive via FastAPI). FastAPI pins starlette <0.42,
# while the fixes require starlette 0.49+/1.x, so there is no FastAPI-compatible
# upstream fix at this time. Risk is mitigated in this deployment:
#   - services are not internet-exposed (NGINX Ingress + default-deny NetworkPolicies)
#   - StaticFiles / UNC-path and Range-merging vectors are not used by these services
# Tracked to be cleared on the next FastAPI major upgrade that adopts patched starlette.
CVE-2025-62727
CVE-2026-48818
CVE-2026-54283

# langchain-core / langsmith HIGH advisories with no fix in the pinned 0.3.x line.
# Remediated by upgrade instead of ignore: the CRITICAL RCE (CVE-2025-68664) and two
# HIGH deserialization/injection flaws (CVE-2025-65106, CVE-2026-44843) are cleared by
# langchain-core 0.3.85. The three below require langchain-core 1.x / langsmith 0.8.x
# (a major migration) AND target features aiops-engine does not use:
#   - CVE-2026-34070: legacy load_prompt() path traversal; the engine uses
#     ChatPromptTemplate only, never load_prompt().
#   - CVE-2026-45134 / GHSA-f4xh-w4cj-qxq8 (langsmith): LangSmith Hub prompt pulls and
#     TracingMiddleware; the engine enables neither (no LANGCHAIN_TRACING).
# Tracked for the langchain-core 1.x migration.
CVE-2026-34070
CVE-2026-45134
GHSA-f4xh-w4cj-qxq8
